Module org.monarchinitiative.phenol.annotations
Package org.monarchinitiative.phenol.annotations.base.temporal

Interface Age

All Superinterfaces:
PointInTime, TemporalInterval, TimelineAware
public interface Age extends PointInTime, TemporalInterval
Age is a PointInTime with associated ConfidenceRange. The Age can be precise or imprecise based on the associated ConfidenceRange. The ConfidenceRange also allows to interpret the Age as a TemporalInterval. Precise Age has TemporalInterval.length() equal to 0, while imprecise Age has TemporalInterval.length() equal to 0 + len(cr), where cr is confidenceRange().

As is the case of the PointInTime, Age has a day precision.

    • compare

      static int compare(Age x, Age y)
      A comparator-like function for default sorting of Age instances.

      The Ages are first compared based on the PointInTime attributes. In case of a tie, the Ages are compared based on the ConfidenceRange, where the Age with a narrower ConfidenceRange is better/greater.
